post_text:
This past week, our scholars wrote to local legislators reinforcing the call to condemn and reform the system that is crippling our communities. #BreonnaTaylor is another reason why. Her death cannot and will not be in vain. Yesterday, Louisville Metro Council banned the use of "no-knock" warrants. Additionally, Sen. Rand Paul introduced a bill, The Justice for Breonna Taylor Act, calling for similar actions at a National level. However, the work is not finished - the officers must be charged and arrested now.
This is why Social Justice is at the root of our curriculum every single day. We must continue to share her story and demand action from our government. #SayHerName #JusticeforBreonnaTaylor #WeWillChangetheWorld

post_text:
Meet Justin McLendon, a senior in the 2020 graduating class of Capital Prep Harbor Upper School. Justin has been a CPREP scholar for 2 years. He has partipcated in track, cross country and baseball.

His social justice project focuses on the lack of recycling.
His goal is to raise awareness on the importance of recycling to the environment.

He was accepted to 8 colleges and received about $88,000 in scholarships. Justin has committed to attending the University of New Haven and wants to major in communications. Specifically, journalism with a minor in media arts.

Justin says, " Capital Prep has taught him how to be a problem solver and become more active."

One piece of advice he has for future Cprep graduates is, " Never isolate yourself from people who want to help you, especially your illuminators."

His favorite memory at Capital Prep was, " establishing new friendships with people in CPREP and building supportive relationships with illuminators like Ms. Johnson and Ms. Luciano."

CONGRATULATIONS JUSTIN!

#WEARECAPITALPREP
#CPREPSENIORCLASS2020
#SENIORSHOUTOUTS
#HARBORSTRONG

post_text:
Dear Families:

We hope all is well with you during these difficult times.

This afternoon Gov. Lamont announced that schools will remain closed through the remainder of the school year. To ensure that Capital Prep’s scholars and families continue to receive academic, social, and emotional support, our distance learning will continue through our scheduled last day of June 19th.

Communications will continue to be updated via ParentSquare, the Parent Portal on our website, and our Social Media.

Stay safe,

Dr. Ayanna Carter and Ronald Hawkins
Capital Prep Harbor

To ensure that Capital Prep’s scholars and families continue to receive academic, social, and emotional support, our distance learning will continue through our scheduled last day of June 19th.

Communications will continue to be updated via ParentSquare, the Parent Portal on our website, and our Social Media.

Stay safe,

Dr. Ayanna Carter and Ronald Hawkins
Capital Prep Harbor

shared_text:
Calvin M Jones II is feeling pumped.
May 1 at 11:53 PM ·

Some know the story and some don't but really long story short, 17 years ago I had to make a decision to finish college right after Cierra was born( 14 days). I was in NC and she was here in CT. I was only able to see her once a month or when her and her mother could visit me, which was only once. You see ....I had to finish school, for this piece of me I just created to have a chance!
At 1 year of age Cierra attended my graduation and watched me recieve my degree from North Carolina A&T SU and God knew that was the beginning of a legacy.

I am almost in tears to announce that my princess committed to my Alma mater .............
North Carolina A&T State University!!! AGGIE PRIDE !!! #aggieclassof2003

Cierra Monét I am so proud of your hard work and effort. Continue to grow and learn baby Girl. You are a Queen ....ALWAYS!!

(Shout out to Teshena Best Debrew inbetween me and cierra... she was my leader in admissions when I went to A&T ...full circle back to aggieland)
#aggiefamily

Up to 30,000 eligible small businesses in more than 30 countries where they operate will be able to receive the grant. To be eligible to apply, you must:

Have between 2 and 50 employees
Have been in business for over a year
Have experienced challenges from COVID-19
Be in or near a location where Facebook operates

Dear Families:

As previously communicated, and following the announcement today, we are following the closure of the Bridgeport Public School District. With that, we will close our Harbor Upper and Lower campuses tomorrow, March 13, and enter next week with our regularly scheduled Spring Break through Friday. Bridgeport Public Schools are closed for the week as well, and we will update you over the break if our closure will be extended into the week of March 23.

Spring Break work will be posted on the website under the Parent Portal.

If you have any questions regarding our operations during this time, please use the email info@wearecapitalprep.org. This email will be regularly monitored, and will be responded to within 3 hours from 8am-6pm, or within 24 hours if after 6pm.

Best Regards,

Capital Prep Harbor Administration

Girls Who Code - Free HS Summer Opportunity in NYC & CT! Deadline March 13th!
The Girls Who Code Summer Immersion Program (SIP) is in its final days for recruitment!
This Summer Immersion Program is a free 7-week introductory computer science program for 10th-11th grade girls going into their junior or senior year of high school. During the 7-week program, participants learn about computer science, gain exposure to tech jobs, and join a sisterhood of girls who are using computer science to become change-makers.
